6.01	Event-related_potentials	Event-related potential	An event-related potential (ERP) is any measured brain response that is directly the result of a thought or perception. More formally, it is any stereotyped electrophysiological response to an internal or external stimulus.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/ac/ComponentsofERP.svg/220px-ComponentsofERP.svg.png
